   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>4.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>The Heart of the King</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>and of the Princes Failing</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The heart of the king and of the princes will fail; the priests will be appalled, and the prophets will be astounded v. 9 .</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>5.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The Sword Reaching to the Soul</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>In verse 10 Jehovah says that the sword reaches to the soul.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>6.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>A Hot Wind Coming from Him</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>A hot wind, a wind too strong for winnowing or for purging, will come from Jehovah vv.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>11-12 .</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>This is another indication that God will send all kinds of calamities to chastise rebellious Israel.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>7.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The Enemy Coming Up like Clouds</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The enemy comes up like clouds, and his chariots like the whirlwind; his horses are swifter than eagles v. 13 . This is a description of the swiftness of the Babylonian army.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>8.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Besiegers Coming from a Distant Land</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>According to verse 16b, besiegers are coming from a distant land, giving out their voice against the cities of Judah.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>9.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>The Sound of the Trumpet Being Heard</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>In verse 19b Jehovah tells them that they hear the sound of the trumpet, the alarm of war.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>10.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Destruction upon Destruction</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Devastating the Whole Land</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Destruction upon destruction will devastate the whole land v. 20 . What calamities there will be!</S>
   </TEXT>
  </BODY>
